\cf2 \strokec2 Would you like to know which of these technology stacks is easiest to replicate if you were trying to build a smaller, niche version of a SaaS platform?\
So based on this demo what is your advice for me as a starting setup as a minimum to be scaled "or scalable plan" ?\
\
You are absolutely asking the right question. The "big names" use complex, custom architectures because they have millions of users. You do 
\f1\b not
\f0\b0  want to start there. That is a trap called "premature optimization."\
Based on the technologies we just discussed, here is your 
\f1\b Minimum Scalable Setup
\f0\b0  (often called the "Golden Stack" for modern SaaS). This stack is easy to build alone or with a small team, but it uses the same fundamental "Lego blocks" as the giants, so you can scale it up later without rewriting everything.\
