\f1\b\fs28 \cf2 \strokec2 2. The Architecture Flow (How it works under the hood)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 Do not try to make the AI write every single WordPress PHP file from scratch (functions.php, header.php, etc.). It will make mistakes.\
Instead, use the 
\f1\b "Injection Method."
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 \strokec2 Step A: The "Base Theme" (Your Asset)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 \strokec2 You (the developer) create a blank, stripped-down WordPress starter theme. It has a standard \cf3 \cb12 \strokec3 index.php\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , \cf3 \cb12 \strokec3 style.css\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , and \cf3 \cb12 \strokec3 functions.php\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 .\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0
\f2\i \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Crucial Logic:
\f0\i0  In this theme, the content areas utilize Tailwind CSS classes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 Step B: The Generation Process (User Flow)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls10\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Input:
\f0\b0  User says "I want a Coffee Shop site, warm colors, modern font."\
\ls10\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 AI Prompting:
\f0\b0  Your backend sends this to GPT-4o. You ask the AI 
\f2\i not
\f0\i0  to write PHP, but to write 
\f1\b HTML components
\f0\b0  using Tailwind CSS (e.g., a Hero Section, a Feature Grid).\
\ls10\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Preview:
\f0\b0  Your Next.js frontend takes that HTML and displays it in 3 different windows (Option A, B, C).\
\ls10\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Selection:
\f0\b0  User clicks "Option B."\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 Step C: The Assembly (The SaaS Magic)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Mapping:
\f0\b0  Your Node.js backend takes the HTML from Option B.\
\ls11\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Injection:
\f0\b0  It opens your "Base Theme" files in memory. It injects the AI-generated HTML into the \cf3 \cb12 \strokec3 <body>\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  of the \cf3 \cb12 \strokec3 index.php\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  (or \cf3 \cb12 \strokec3 front-page.php\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 ).\
\ls11\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Zipping:
\f0\b0  It uses the 
\f1\b Archiver
\f0\b0  library to bundle this modified Base Theme into \cf3 \cb12 \strokec3 theme-coffee-shop.zip\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 .\
\ls11\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Delivery:
\f0\b0  The browser initiates the download.\
