\cf2 The "Attempt Recovery" error is the #1 trust-killer in AI website builders. It appears when the 
\f1\b HTML in the database
\f0\b0  does not match the 
\f1\b HTML the React Block expects
\f0\b0  exactly (even a single extra space or a mismatched class can trigger it).\
To "harden" your system and prevent this error from ever appearing, you should implement these 3 layers of defense, ordered from easiest to most robust.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf2 1. The "Sandbox" Method (Use \cf3 \cb12 \strokec3 core/html\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 )\
